cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SD, cs.IR 

This paper is about pruning parameters from N-gram backoff language models, which is a common technique in natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of relative entropy as a measure for pruning, which is a concept from information theory and machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. Additionally, the paper proposes a simple pruning criterion based on perplexity, which is a common evaluation metric in NLP, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible category. The paper also involves experiments and comparisons with other pruning methods, which could fall under cs.SD (Software Engineering) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
